-- Liberia Says IMF Capital Markets Unit Gives Backing to Sell Treasury Bills
-- Ansu Konneh
-- 2010-07-19T01:44:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/liberia-says-imf-capital-markets-unit-gives-backing-to-sell-treasury-bills.html

          
          
             Liberia has been qualified by the
International Monetary Fund’s Money and Capital Markets
Development unit to introduction a treasury bill for the first
time, according to a statement from the West African nation.   
 “We recently created a Treasury Operations Section and
have been providing the staff with the requisite training and
resources to ensure the Bank’s preparedness for such
operations,” Central Bank of Liberia Governor Mills Jones told
reporters in Monrovia.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
